"t_title20","〈台北都會〉里長轟砍長者補助 柯不發一語
        
            
        
    "," 2018年6月13日•星期三•戊戌年四月卅"," 為達最佳瀏覽效果，建議使用 Chrome、Firefox 或 Internet Explorer 10(含) 以上版本的瀏覽器。 爆  〔記者沈佩瑤／台北報導〕不滿柯市府上任取消重陽敬老金，又提高長者健保補助年齡門檻，內湖區大湖里長洪美惠昨向市長柯文哲陳情，痛批市府政策「完全不夠公平正義」，更批敬老卡只補助交通費，就像「買豬肉便當給回教徒吃」，長者出門難道不用吃喝？還不如待在家省錢；面對里長砲火猛烈，柯卻不發一語，北市社會局回應，因財源有限，目前不考慮調降補助門檻。 凡設籍北市滿一年、七十歲以上，且綜合所得稅率廿％以下，可申請健保補助每月最多七四九元。社會局表示，中央僅補助中低收長者，而綜合所得稅率廿％以下多半為弱勢近貧家庭，因此以公務預算及公益彩券盈餘支應。以二○一七年為例，全市有四十四萬名六十五歲以上長者，其中廿一萬一八五四人接受健保補助，總經費約十六億元。 柯文哲昨主持內湖區里長座談會，洪美惠批評，她連兩年協助推動老人共餐政策，但最多不過五、六十人參與，里內還有六百多名長者享受不到，市長立意良善，但應該要思考配套措施，例如重陽敬老金，是否能考慮只刪除三分之二或三分之一，讓老人還有五百、一千元可用，至少能帶兒孫出門同樂。 洪美惠直言，敬老卡只補助交通費，「就像買豬肉便當給回教徒吃，用不到啊！」因為長者認為一旦出門，就會有各式消費，待在家一天可能只要生活費一百元。柯市府還提高長者申請健保補助的年齡門檻，洪怒斥「完全不夠公平正義」，盼能研議恢復部分補助。 社會局會後表示，北市六十五歲以上人口約四十四萬，三年後將成長到五十萬人，占北市總人口廿％，由於北市老年人口快速增加，在有限資源做合理分配下，經評估後才會調整補助門檻為七十歲，因此目前不考慮調降。 台北市長柯文哲昨主持內湖區里長座談會，里長洪美惠痛批市府政策「完全不夠公平正義」。（記者方賓照攝） 新聞送上來！快加入自由電子報APP、LINE好友  2018年6月13日•星期三•戊戌年四月卅 注目新聞 1 中國卡車罷工延燒 司機高喊「打倒共產黨」！ 2 新版身分證票選出爐 設計師魯少綸奪首獎！ 3 洋腸又來！夜店外帶18歲妹 網站取名「台女很容易」... 4 侯友宜妻1塊土地99個門牌 蘇貞昌：太荒唐 5 連俞涵超正弟媳曝光…根本巨乳林志玲！","230"
"t_title21","〈台北都會〉《一期工程無法容納》環南市場336攤 恐休3年
        
            
        
    "," 2018年6月13日•星期三•戊戌年四月卅"," 為達最佳瀏覽效果，建議使用 Chrome、Firefox 或 Internet Explorer 10(含) 以上版本的瀏覽器。 爆  〔記者楊心慧／台北報導〕台北市環南市場改建案被視為市長柯文哲任內重要政績之一，環南市場改建第一期工程預計明年八月完工，但一期工程完工後，卻只能容納九八七家攤商，竟有三三六攤商無處可去，北市市場處坦言尚與攤商協商中；北市議員郭昭巖則痛批，台北市政府作法不合理，怎能要攤商休息三年？認為此舉侵害攤商權益。 環南市場為大台北地區重要採買市場，擁有一三二三攤商，因環境髒亂、設備老舊，屢次提出改建，歷經三任市長、延宕十八年，終於在柯文哲任內開工改建，北市府投入五十八億元，規劃改建工程分成一、二期，上週柯還大動作主持第一期工程上梁典禮。 市場處指出，攤商先在舊環南市場中營業，等到明年八月一期工程完工後，會讓攤商移入，第二階段則在二○二二年三月啟用。有攤商抱怨，一期工程根本無法容納全部攤商，只能讓九八七家進駐，剩下的三三六家，市府希望休業三年，待二期完工後再回來開業。 郭昭巖認為，三百多攤要停業未免太多，除非是對方願意休息才能裁撤，市府不能因為改建方便，硬剝奪攤商的權益！對此，市場處科長何相慶坦言，有三三六攤須停業，等蓋好後再回來，正與攤商商量。 至於需休業的三三六家攤商主要為哪些？何相慶說，先詢問有意願停業的攤商，剩下依照他們的營業狀況評估，例如是否為天天營業等；記者詢問，若攤商不願休業怎麼辦？何說，應該不會有這狀況，目前仍在協調。 環南市場自治會長陳正宗說，協調停業的攤商大多本身未營業，像是租給其他攤商擺放冰箱、或是因年紀大轉讓給其他人經營等。至於協調狀況？陳說，目前尚未完全協商好，還有部分攤商正在協調中。 郭昭巖表示，市府應尊重攤商意願，除非是整年都沒在營運，才能要求對方停業，有些年紀大的攤商，礙於身體狀況，僅賺生活所需，並非每天營業，但市府不能要求人家休息三年，這不合理。 環南市場第一期工程完工後，只能容納九百八十七家攤商，竟有三百三十六攤無處可去。（資料照，記者黃建豪攝） 環南市場改建，攤商會先在舊環南市場中營業。（資料照，記者黃建豪攝） 新聞送上來！快加入自由電子報APP、LINE好友  2018年6月13日•星期三•戊戌年四月卅 注目新聞 1 中國卡車罷工延燒 司機高喊「打倒共產黨」！ 2 新版身分證票選出爐 設計師魯少綸奪首獎！ 3 洋腸又來！夜店外帶18歲妹 網站取名「台女很容易」... 4 侯友宜妻1塊土地99個門牌 蘇貞昌：太荒唐 5 連俞涵超正弟媳曝光…根本巨乳林志玲！","229"
"t_title22","《TAIPEI TIMES》 Five incumbents lack majority support
        
            
        
    "," 2018年6月13日•星期三•戊戌年四月卅"," 為達最佳瀏覽效果，建議使用 Chrome、Firefox 或 Internet Explorer 10(含) 以上版本的瀏覽器。 爆  FADING GREEN? The ‘Global Views’ survey found that DPP local government heads appear to have become less popular than their KMT and independent counterparts By Stacy Hsu / Staff reporter Five of the 14 local government heads seeking re-election in November’s nine-in-one elections do not have majority backing from their electorates, including independent Taipei Mayor Ko Wen-je （柯文哲） and Taichung Mayor Lin Chia-lung （林佳龍） of the Democratic Progressive Party （DPP）, a survey released yesterday by the Chinese-language monthly Global Views showed. The poll did not include Tainan, as it is governed by Acting Tainan Mayor Lee Meng-yan （李孟諺） after former Tainan mayor William Lai （賴清德） became premier in September last year. However, Presidential Office Secretary-General Chen Chu （陳菊） was included, as she did not leave her post as Kaohsiung mayor until after the poll was conducted from Feb. 23 to March 29. Ko garnered a support rating of 48.9 percent, making him one of the five mayors and county commissioners whose re-election bids failed to receive majority support from their electorates, the survey found. Ko was followed by Changhua County Commissioner Wei Ming-ku （魏明谷） of the DPP with a support rating of 47.9 percent, Lin with 44.3 percent, Chiayi Mayor Twu Shiing-jer （涂醒哲） of the DPP with 37.6 percent and Penghu County Commissioner Chen Kuang-fu （陳光復） of the DPP with 34.2 percent, the poll showed. The three incumbents seeking re-election who obtained the highest support were Lienchiang County Commissioner Liu Tseng-ying （劉增應） of the Chinese Nationalist Party （KMT） with 69.9 percent, Taoyuan Mayor Cheng Wen-tsan （鄭文燦） of the DPP with 68.3 percent and Pingtung County Commissioner Pan Men-an （潘孟安） of the DPP with 65.9 percent, the survey showed. In terms of governance performance, Cheng received the highest approval rating at 77.9 percent among all 20 local government heads, followed by Liu at 77.4 percent and independent Hualien County Commissioner Fu Kun-chi （傅崑萁）, who has reached the two-term limit, at 77.2 percent, the poll found. The worst performers were Lin at 49 percent, Twu at 45.9 percent and Chen Kuang-fu at 40.1 percent, the survey found. DPP mayors and county commissioners appeared to have become less popular than their KMT and independent counterparts, who received an average approval rating of 65 percent and 64.2 percent respectively, compared with 60.1 percent for DPP leaders, the poll found. KMT and independent local heads received an average score of 70.7 and 69.6 respectively out of 100 for governance performance, while DPP mayors and county commissioners were given an average score of 67.7, the poll showed. Asked what would be the best next step for the six mayors and county commissioners stepping down this year, most respondents in New Taipei City said they would like to see New Taipei City Mayor Eric Chu （朱立倫） of the KMT assume an important party post （16.9 percent） or run for president （15.8 percent）. Most respondents in Taitung County said that Taitung County Commissioner Justin Huang （黃健庭） of the KMT should run for a legislative seat, while most respondents in Kaohsiung supported Chen Chu becoming a Cabinet member. Regarding Hsinchu County Commissioner Chiu Ching-chun （邱鏡淳） of the KMT and Chiayi County Commissioner Helen Chang （張花冠） of the DPP, most respondents in their respective electorates said they hoped to see them retire after their terms expire. The poll collected 14,347 valid samples and has a confidence level of 95 percent, with a margin of error of between 3.7 and 6.9 percentage points. 新聞來源：TAIPEI TIMES 
Taichung Mayor Lin Chia-lung, center, poses for photographers at an event in Taichung yesterday.
